data.title: Eloise Mumford

data.text: Actress Eloise Mumford got her start in acting when she was just 13 years old. In 2008, she made her Broadway debut in the revival of "Speed-the-Plow." In 2009, she made her film debut in "Some Boys Don't Leave." Mumford's early acting roles were in dramatic series like "Law & Order: Special Victims Unit" (NBC, 1999-), "Crash" (Starz, 2008-2010) and "Mercy" (NBC, 2009-2010). She also appeared in "Lone Star" (Fox, 2010-11). Her work around this time also included a part on the TV movie "Christmas with Holly" (ABC, 2012-13). In the 2010s, she acted in the action-packed comedy "So Undercover" (2013) with Miley Cyrus and "Drones" (2014). She also worked in television around this time, including a part on "The River" (ABC, 2011-12). In the 2010s, she then appeared in the Gina Carano thriller "In the Blood" (2014), "Not Safe For Work" (2014) and the Dakota Johnson blockbuster dramatic adaptation "Fifty Shades of Grey" (2015). Most recently, Mumford appeared in "Just In Time For Christmas" (Hallmark Channel, 2015-).
